1.title: Ali & Justin
1.plot: A career-driven fashion stylist, Ali is often at odds with the more frugal Justin, an accountant with his sights set on growing their family. Now free from distraction, they are left to focus on each other and contemplate their future.

2.title: Farah, Beth & Isabel
2.plot: Three best friends living a free-spirited Hollywood lifestyle choose to give up all their possessions. Along they way they discover surprising things about themselves, their career paths and their relationships with each other.

3.title: Ariana & Ryan
3.plot: Fitness model, Ariana, and her school teacher boyfriend, Ryan, have their relationship put to an intense test. In the end, they must decide if their bond is strong enough to make it.

4.title: Autianna & Jaseena
4.plot: Two single sisters, Autianna and Jaseena-who share an apartment, a bartending job and frivolous spending habits-need a major wake up call. Will these sisters discover what it takes to become responsible adults?

5.title: Rai and Patty
5.plot: Rai and Patty, a newly married couple from different backgrounds, cope with being stripped differently, but both look to open doors to new chapters in their lives. By the end, they uncover unexpected truths about themselves and each other.

6.title: Russ & Ariel
6.plot: A ladies' man and his recently-divorced roommate are pushed to their breaking points when they are left with an empty house and a sick cat. Tempers flare as they learn to cope with sharing their living space in ways they never expected.

7.title: Brian & Jason
7.plot: Brian and Jason, who have been together 15 years, hope that giving up all they own will help them reconnect and finally set a wedding a date. Will the stress of their experience drive them apart or remind them why they first fell in love?

8.title: Richie Skye
8.plot: Recent LA transplant and social media aficionado, Richie Skye, looks to find balance between the glamorous life he portrays online and the reality he has been avoiding.

imdb.plot outline: Based on the hit Scandinavian format, this outlandish yet emotional social experiment aims to discover how people's lives and values change once everything they own is stripped away. This new series exposes people's relationships with their personal belongings as they forego everything they own - clothing, furniture, money and all coveted possessions - for 21 days. Each day, they may retrieve one item that they cannot live without, and priorities will inevitably emerge. Expected to go about their daily lives by showing up to work, maintaining their families and keeping up with social circles - without their everyday necessities - each person jumps into survival mode in order to determine what is most essential to them. With no shortage of outrageous and uncomfortable moments along the way, this trans-formative journey has a life-changing impact as they each uncover what truly matters to them most.
